GIT-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
git practice
git config --global user.name “kumar”
git config --global user.email  “kalva.kumar@gmail.com”
Git init
Git add .
Git commit -m “comit name”
Git branch -M main
Git remote add origin url
Git push -u origin main


Git init --> it will create new local git repository
Git clone --> used to copy a repository
Git add --> add a files to staging area
Git commit --> will create a snap shot of changes & save it to the git directory
Git push --> push local changes to the origin
Git fetch à get all the changes from the origin (No merge)
Git pull à  get all the changes from origin and merge
git checkout -- filename --> undo the inside the file content/discard changes done in a file in workspace
git log --> check the commit logs
git stash --> temporary storage area
git branch --> list the branches
git branch -b branchName --> create and enter new branch
git branch -d branchName --> delete the branch name
Git checkout branchname --> enter the new branch



Class-2 Advanced level

Git log --> logs history
Git log -p --> show the edit commit
Git log --oneline
Git log --oneline --all --> show all commit ids
Git fetch origin master --> just adding not applying
Git pull origin master --> coming & applying
Git merge branch name
Su -kumar --> swich to kumar user 

Git stash save file --> save the index storage
Git stash list --> show the list
Git stash pop --> role back
Git stash apply --> not deleting stash memory
Git stash drop --> delete the stash memory

Cat > file name
Cat >> file name

Types of users
Owner
Group
Others

Types of permissions
Reed - r --> 4
Write - w --> 2
Execute - X --> 1

4+2+1 = 7 
Chmod 777 f1 --> rwxrwxrwx --> given all permitions
-rw-r--r-- 1 kalva 197609 1678 Apr  7 16:19 devops.pem --> 644
Chmod 770 --> given the permissions to owner user not others
0 --> means no permissions
1 --> X
2 -->  W
3 --> W+X
4 --> r
5 --> r+x
6 --> r+w
7 --> r+w+x



Linux----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1. *Linux Basic Commands:*

	- ls:- List directory contents.
	- cd:- Change the current directory.
	- pwd:- Print working directory.
	- mkdir:- Create a new directory.
	- touch:- Create a new empty file.
	- vi :- text editor
	- cat :- to check file content
	- rmdir:- Remove a directory.
	- cp:- Copy files and directories.
	- mv:- Move/rename files and directories.
	- rm:- Remove files or directories.rm -r, rm -f, rm -rf file name
	- Top :- display Linux tasks
	- Ping :- verify the network connection
	- cal :- display the monthly calendar
	- Hello :- to display brief system info
	- Help :- to display list of commands
	- Clear :- to clear the terminal
	- Whoami :- check the current user
	- Exit :- to logout the session
	- Ctrl+alt+t :- to open the terminal
	- Ctrl+d :- to close the terminal
	- Ctrl + insert :- copy
	- Shift + insert :- past
	- Ctrl + c :- exit
	File system navigation commands
	- Cd . :-changes to current directory
	- Cd .. :- changes to parent directory
	- Cd/cd~  :- changes to user home directory
	- Cd - :- changes to previous working directory
	- Chmod :- change the access control list
	- Chown :- change file owner & group
	- Sudo :- superuser do





